1
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:09,958
- ( theme music playing )

2
00:00:32,291 --> 00:00:33,291
♪ OH! ♪

3
00:00:37,166 --> 00:00:38,125
♪ OH! ♪

4
00:01:23,833 --> 00:01:24,958
♪ OH! ♪

5
00:01:28,541 --> 00:01:29,666
♪ OH! ♪

6
00:01:39,291 --> 00:01:42,791
- Milly: DEAR MOM, DAD,
BIG BIG SISTER,

7
00:01:42,875 --> 00:01:45,458
MIDDLE BIG SISTER,
LITTLE BIG SISTER,

8
00:01:45,541 --> 00:01:48,083
BIG BIG BROTHER,
MIDDLE BIG BROTHER,

9
00:01:48,166 --> 00:01:50,916
LITTLE BIG BROTHER,
DOUGIE, ANRI,

10
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:54,333
RODNEY, MIKEY
AND LITTLE SANDRA.

11
00:01:54,416 --> 00:01:56,875
HOW ARE YOU?
I'M DOING JUST FINE.

12
00:01:56,958 --> 00:01:59,791
( yawns )
GOOD MORNING. I'M SLEEPY.

13
00:02:01,333 --> 00:02:03,041
- MILLY, YOU STAYED
UP ALL NIGHT...

14
00:02:03,125 --> 00:02:05,208
- ...WRITING HOME TO YOUR
FAMILY AGAIN, DIDN'T YOU?

15
00:02:05,291 --> 00:02:06,958
- ( nervous chuckle )
- THAT'S WHAT HAPPENS

16
00:02:07,041 --> 00:02:08,500
WHEN YOU WRITE
TO EACH OF THEM SEPARATELY,

17
00:02:08,583 --> 00:02:10,458
DOWN TO THE LAST
LITTLE NIECE AND NEPHEW.

18
00:02:10,541 --> 00:02:12,916
- TADAH!
AT LEAST IT PAYS OFF.

19
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:14,083
I'M GETTING RAVE REVIEWS.

20
00:02:14,166 --> 00:02:15,666
THEY CALL MY LETTERS
"THE MILLY MONTHLY."

21
00:02:15,750 --> 00:02:18,500
- QUALITY ASIDE, YOU COULD'VE
WRITTEN SEVERAL BOOKS BY NOW.

22
00:02:18,583 --> 00:02:20,833
- WHAT'S SO WEIRD ABOUT THAT?
DON'T YOU WRITE HOME?

23
00:02:20,916 --> 00:02:22,458
- UH...

24
00:02:22,541 --> 00:02:24,583
YEAH, WELL,
I USED TO WRITE AT FIRST,

25
00:02:24,666 --> 00:02:25,875
BUT IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME.

26
00:02:25,958 --> 00:02:27,833
BUT I THINK FOR MOST PEOPLE,
THAT'S NORMAL.

27
00:02:27,916 --> 00:02:30,708
BESIDES, WHAT WOULD
THEY SAY IF I TOLD THEM

28
00:02:30,791 --> 00:02:33,041
I WAS HANGING OUT
WITH VASH THE STAMPEDE?

29
00:02:33,125 --> 00:02:35,333
- SO YOU JUST DON'T WANT
TO WRITE, MERYL?

30
00:02:35,416 --> 00:02:37,666
IT'S NOT THAT I DON'T WANT
TO WRITE TO THEM.

31
00:02:40,458 --> 00:02:42,208
I GUESS
IT SOUNDS PRETTY LAME

32
00:02:42,291 --> 00:02:44,041
TO SAY THAT
I JUST DON'T HAVE THE TIME.

33
00:02:44,125 --> 00:02:45,791
- ( gunfire )
- ( both gasp )

34
00:02:47,750 --> 00:02:49,500
( both yell )

35
00:02:55,750 --> 00:02:57,625
- ( people gasp,
chattering )

36
00:02:57,708 --> 00:02:59,333
- OH GEE, SORRY ABOUT THAT.

37
00:02:59,416 --> 00:03:01,750
I MUST'VE ACCIDENTALLY
PULLED THE TRIGGER.

38
00:03:01,833 --> 00:03:03,125
- HOW DARE YOU!

39
00:03:03,208 --> 00:03:05,458
YOU HAVE A LOT OF NERVE,
YOU IMPUDENT SCOUNDREL!

40
00:03:05,541 --> 00:03:07,500
- WE'RE NOT DUMB ENOUGH
TO BE SCARED BY YOU

41
00:03:07,583 --> 00:03:08,791
AND YOUR ROTTEN FRIENDS!

42
00:03:08,875 --> 00:03:10,666
- OH YES, IT'S BECOME
CLEAR TO ME NOW.

43
00:03:10,750 --> 00:03:13,041
THERE'S A LOT OF MEANING
BEHIND THOSE WORDS, FRIENDS.

44
00:03:13,125 --> 00:03:15,000
SO STAND UP WITH
YOUR HEADS HELD HIGH

45
00:03:15,083 --> 00:03:16,500
AND SAY WHAT YOU WANT TO SAY!

46
00:03:16,583 --> 00:03:18,916
- WE WON'T GIVE UP OUR LAND
NO MATTER WHAT YOU DO TO US!

47
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,791
- YEAH, WE'RE NOT GONNA
TAKE THIS ANYMORE,

48
00:03:20,875 --> 00:03:22,416
AND YOU CAN GO BACK
AND TELL THAT TO MORGAN!

49
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:24,291
- DID YOU HEAR WHAT I SAID,
YOU OLD GEEZERS?

50
00:03:24,375 --> 00:03:25,583
- HEY, COME ON NOW.

51
00:03:25,666 --> 00:03:28,291
MY GUN WENT OFF BY MISTAKE.
YOU KNOW THAT.

52
00:03:28,375 --> 00:03:31,750
- Old man: A MISTAKE MY ASS,
YOU FAT-LIPPED GOLEM!

53
00:03:31,833 --> 00:03:34,541
- WHAT?
WHAT DID YOU SAY?

54
00:03:34,625 --> 00:03:35,833
A GOLEM?  HA!

55
00:03:35,916 --> 00:03:38,000
I'M LAUGHING SO HARD,

56
00:03:38,083 --> 00:03:39,750
MY PISTOL'S TWITCHING.

57
00:03:42,625 --> 00:03:45,416
- ( both yell, grunt )

58
00:03:49,708 --> 00:03:52,333
- YOU HAVE NO IDEA
HOW DANGEROUS THAT WAS!

59
00:03:52,416 --> 00:03:55,250
( humphs )
IF YOU MAKE THIS BROOM HEAD MAD,

60
00:03:55,333 --> 00:03:57,041
I GUARANTEE HE'LL LEAVE YOU
WITH A LOT MORE

61
00:03:57,125 --> 00:03:59,000
THAN INJURIES
AND PROPERTY DAMAGE.

62
00:03:59,083 --> 00:04:00,416
GOOD GOD!

63
00:04:00,500 --> 00:04:01,875
- YOU'RE THE ONES
WHO ARE DANGEROUS,

64
00:04:01,958 --> 00:04:03,666
CLOTHESLINING HIM
FROM BEHIND LIKE THAT!

65
00:04:03,750 --> 00:04:05,750
- ( chattering continues )
- ( clatters )

66
00:04:05,833 --> 00:04:07,875
- HUH?
- ( creaking )

67
00:04:07,958 --> 00:04:10,958
- ( screams, whimpers )

68
00:04:12,125 --> 00:04:13,916
- MERYL,
THAT'S A SMALL SACRIFICE

69
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:16,375
FOR A GREAT CAUSE.
- I KNOW!  THAT'S RIGHT!

70
00:04:16,458 --> 00:04:19,750
- WAY TO GO, MILLY!
- THAT'S ALL YOU'VE GOT TO SAY?

71
00:04:21,125 --> 00:04:24,208
- DID YOU SAY BODYGUARDS?
- EXACTLY.

72
00:04:24,291 --> 00:04:26,083
IF YOU TWO WERE HERE
TO PROTECT US,

73
00:04:26,166 --> 00:04:28,208
WE'D FEEL A WHOLE LOT SAFER.
- I'M SORRY.

74
00:04:28,291 --> 00:04:30,125
THANKS, ANYWAY,
BUT COMPANY REGULATIONS

75
00:04:30,208 --> 00:04:32,541
STRICTLY FORBID US
FROM TAKING ANY PART-TIME JOBS.

76
00:04:32,625 --> 00:04:35,791
- I UNDERSTAND. HOW ABOUT
YOU, SON? ARE YOU INTERESTED?

77
00:04:35,875 --> 00:04:37,625
- WHY THE HELL
ARE YOU ASKING HIM?!

78
00:04:37,708 --> 00:04:40,333
- THE WAY THAT HE MOVED
WHEN HE PROTECTED US BACK THERE,

79
00:04:40,416 --> 00:04:43,166
HE WAS EXCEPTIONALLY BRAVE.
- YOU DON'T SAY!

80
00:04:43,250 --> 00:04:45,291
WELL, IT'S NOTHING.
I DO THE BEST I CAN.

81
00:04:45,375 --> 00:04:48,166
( laughs )
- ABSOLUTELY NO WAY!

82
00:04:48,250 --> 00:04:50,083
( growls )
HOW COULD YOU ASK HIM?!

83
00:04:50,166 --> 00:04:52,041
DON'T YOU KNOW WHO
THIS BROOM HEAD IS, MISTER?

84
00:04:52,125 --> 00:04:53,916
- WHAT IS IT, LITTLE LADY?
YOU WANT THE JOB NOW?

85
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:56,666
- ( whimpering )
- WOW, THAT'S GREAT.

86
00:04:56,750 --> 00:04:58,375
ONLY YOU WOULD THINK
OF USING YOUR POSITION

87
00:04:58,458 --> 00:05:00,416
TO HELP OUT PEOPLE
WHO ARE TRULY IN NEED.

88
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:03,375
- UH, WELL,
WE HAVE NO CHOICE.

89
00:05:03,458 --> 00:05:05,625
I THINK THE
SITUATION REPRESENTS

90
00:05:05,708 --> 00:05:07,916
THE CATEGORY OF
RISK-PREVENTION TO THE "T."

91
00:05:10,666 --> 00:05:13,291
WHY HAVE YOU DECIDED
TO COME WITH US, MR. VASH?

92
00:05:13,375 --> 00:05:15,166
- ( chuckling )
WELL, I DON'T KNOW.

93
00:05:15,250 --> 00:05:17,375
I GUESS SOMETHING WAS
BOTHERING ME, THAT'S ALL.

94
00:05:17,458 --> 00:05:19,458
- Meryl: KEEP OUT OF THIS ONE.
DO YOU UNDERSTAND ME?

95
00:05:19,541 --> 00:05:21,083
- Vash: YES, MA'AM.

96
00:05:22,833 --> 00:05:25,333
- YOU SEE THAT?
THAT'S OUR LAND THERE.

97
00:05:25,416 --> 00:05:26,791
- ( Meryl gasps )

98
00:05:31,791 --> 00:05:33,666
- ( birds chirping )

99
00:05:39,791 --> 00:05:41,333
- Meryl:
THIS IS INCREDIBLE.

100
00:05:42,666 --> 00:05:43,875
HOW IS ALL OF THIS HERE

101
00:05:43,958 --> 00:05:45,583
IF THERE'S NO ACCESS TO A SHIP?

102
00:05:45,666 --> 00:05:48,041
- AMAZING.
IT'S JUST LIKE A GEO PLANT.

103
00:05:50,500 --> 00:05:52,000
- NO, IT'S NOT JUST LIKE IT.

104
00:05:52,083 --> 00:05:53,333
THIS IS A GEO PLANT.

105
00:05:54,458 --> 00:05:56,416
- YES, WE BELIEVE
THAT A GEO PLANT

106
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:59,416
RAN ALONG A MINERAL VEIN
TO FORM THIS OFFSHOOT.

107
00:05:59,500 --> 00:06:01,708
THE LAND VALUE HAS
SKYROCKETED SO HIGH,

108
00:06:01,791 --> 00:06:04,333
IT'S WORTH AS MUCH
AS A SHIP 300 YARDS WIDE.

109
00:06:05,666 --> 00:06:07,166
- THAT MAY BE,
BUT IT COULDN'T HAVE GOTTEN

110
00:06:07,250 --> 00:06:08,583
THIS FAR
WITHOUT A LOT OF HELP.

111
00:06:08,666 --> 00:06:10,666
IT WOULD'VE TAKEN
A MASSIVE AMOUNT OF EFFORT.

112
00:06:12,041 --> 00:06:16,083
- I REMEMBER IT CLEARLY,
20 YEARS AGO IT WAS A TINY BUD.

113
00:06:16,166 --> 00:06:18,083
BUT I COULDN'T
BELIEVE MY EYES.

114
00:06:18,166 --> 00:06:20,583
JUST IMAGINING
HOW WE COULD RAISE

115
00:06:20,666 --> 00:06:23,666
SUCH LUSH, BEAUTIFUL LAND
ON AN ARID PLANET LIKE THIS--

116
00:06:23,750 --> 00:06:26,000
YOU HAVE NO IDEA
HOW THAT KEPT US GOING.

117
00:06:28,583 --> 00:06:31,833
THAT'S RIGHT.
OUR LIVES, OUR DREAMS

118
00:06:31,916 --> 00:06:34,375
AND OUR HOPES
ARE ALL HERE.

119
00:06:34,458 --> 00:06:36,625
- IT IS AMAZING
WHAT YOU'VE DONE HERE,

120
00:06:36,708 --> 00:06:38,958
BUT WHAT DOES THIS HAVE TO DO
WITH YOUR HIRING BODYGUARDS?

121
00:06:39,041 --> 00:06:41,250
- YOU SAW WHAT HAPPENED
BACK THERE IN TOWN.

122
00:06:41,333 --> 00:06:43,208
THAT WAS NOT
THE FIRST TIME.

123
00:06:43,291 --> 00:06:44,416
THE LANDOWNER MORGAN

124
00:06:44,500 --> 00:06:46,291
HAS BEEN THREATENING
US TIME AND AGAIN

125
00:06:46,375 --> 00:06:47,750
TO HAND OVER
THE DEED OR ELSE.

126
00:06:49,666 --> 00:06:52,041
BUT THAT IS
ALL GOING TO END TOMORROW.

127
00:06:52,125 --> 00:06:54,208
ONCE WE GET THIS DEED
OVER TO CITY HALL,

128
00:06:54,291 --> 00:06:56,583
THERE'S NOTHING HE CAN DO.

129
00:06:56,666 --> 00:06:58,666
Man: HEY, GUYS,
IT'S TIME TO CHANGE SHIFTS.

130
00:06:58,750 --> 00:07:01,083
- ( door opens )

131
00:07:01,166 --> 00:07:04,125
- OH, IT'S FREEZING OUT THERE.
- IT GETS COLD AT NIGHT.

132
00:07:05,291 --> 00:07:07,541
- I APPRECIATE
ALL OF YOUR HELP.

133
00:07:07,625 --> 00:07:10,041
- HEY, IT'S NO PROBLEM.
SINCE WE WERE LITTLE KIDS,

134
00:07:10,125 --> 00:07:12,583
THIS PLACE HAS ALWAYS BEEN
OUR PLAYGROUND, HUH?

135
00:07:12,666 --> 00:07:14,083
- YEAH, AND WE'RE
NEVER GONNA GIVE IT UP.

136
00:07:14,166 --> 00:07:16,500
- BESIDES, WE GOT THESE 
TWO GORGEOUS GIRLS TONIGHT

137
00:07:16,583 --> 00:07:18,208
TO KEEP US COMPANY.
- ( women laugh nervously )

138
00:07:18,291 --> 00:07:20,583
- YEAH, I ALMOST WISH THAT
MORNING DIDN'T HAVE TO COME.

139
00:07:20,666 --> 00:07:22,166
- ( all laugh )

140
00:07:22,250 --> 00:07:24,958
- THAT REMINDS ME:
WHAT HAPPENED TO THAT BROOM BOY?

141
00:07:25,041 --> 00:07:27,500
- I THOUGHT THAT FOR NOW WE
SHOULD HANDLE THIS WITHOUT HIM.

142
00:07:27,583 --> 00:07:29,500
I TOLD HIM TO GO BACK
TO TOWN IN THE MEANTIME.

143
00:07:29,583 --> 00:07:31,625
- WHAT'S THIS?  A LITTLE FIGHT
WITH THE BOYFRIEND?

144
00:07:31,708 --> 00:07:34,583
- ( coughs )
HE'S NOT MY BOYFRIEND!

145
00:07:34,666 --> 00:07:35,583
- ( both laugh )

146
00:07:35,666 --> 00:07:37,375
- STOP IT. I DON'T
EVEN LIKE HIM.

147
00:07:37,458 --> 00:07:40,041
LET'S GO, MILLY.  WE HAVE
TO GO DO THE ROUNDS NOW.

148
00:07:40,125 --> 00:07:42,541
- COMING!
- HUH?

149
00:07:47,541 --> 00:07:49,041
OH.

150
00:07:53,916 --> 00:07:56,416
- ( shivers )
IT SURE IS COLD.

151
00:07:56,500 --> 00:07:58,208
HEY, MERYL,
IS THERE SOMETHING WRONG?

152
00:07:58,291 --> 00:07:59,500
- IT'S NOTHING, REALLY.

153
00:07:59,583 --> 00:08:01,083
IT'S JUST THAT
I KNOW I'VE SEEN THE FACE

154
00:08:01,166 --> 00:08:02,583
IN THAT PICTURE
SOMEWHERE BEFORE.

155
00:08:02,666 --> 00:08:04,791
THE ONLY THING IS
I CAN'T SEEM TO PLACE IT.

156
00:08:04,875 --> 00:08:07,125
- OH, YOU MEAN LIKE
A PASSING FANCY?

157
00:08:07,208 --> 00:08:08,708
- A PASSING LIKENESS.

158
00:08:08,791 --> 00:08:11,583
I'M ABSOLUTELY SURE
I'VE SEEN THAT FACE BEFORE.

159
00:08:11,666 --> 00:08:13,541
- ( rustling )
- ( guns cock )

160
00:08:13,625 --> 00:08:14,958
Women:
WHO GOES THERE?

161
00:08:15,041 --> 00:08:17,958
OOH.  WAIT.
DON'T SHOOT!

162
00:08:20,166 --> 00:08:21,750
- ( both gasp )
- OH NO, IT'S THAT MAN.

163
00:08:21,833 --> 00:08:23,833
- WELL,
WHAT A PLEASANT SURPRISE--

164
00:08:23,916 --> 00:08:25,291
THE TWO OF YOU ONCE AGAIN.

165
00:08:25,375 --> 00:08:27,291
YOU CAN PUT
YOUR GUNS AWAY, LADIES,

166
00:08:27,375 --> 00:08:29,041
OBVIOUSLY
I'VE COME HERE UNARMED.

167
00:08:29,125 --> 00:08:31,083
- WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING HERE?

168
00:08:31,166 --> 00:08:33,458
- I CAME TO TRY
AND TALK DAD OUT OF THIS.

169
00:08:33,541 --> 00:08:35,500
MORGAN MEANS
BUSINESS THIS TIME.

170
00:08:35,583 --> 00:08:37,958
- "TALK DAD OU--" OH?

171
00:08:42,333 --> 00:08:44,291
AH!  THE PICTURE!

172
00:08:44,375 --> 00:08:47,416
- ( chuckles )
YUP, THAT'S ME, ALL RIGHT.

173
00:08:47,500 --> 00:08:48,875
THE UNWORTHY SON.

174
00:08:48,958 --> 00:08:51,250
NOW WHERE IS HE?
- ( both grunt )

175
00:08:53,125 --> 00:08:55,000
- WHAT REASON
COULD YOU POSSIBLY HAVE

176
00:08:55,083 --> 00:08:56,791
TO POINT A GUN
AT YOUR PARENTS?

177
00:08:56,875 --> 00:08:59,041
- OH.
- IT'S NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS,

178
00:08:59,125 --> 00:09:00,291
BUT IF YOU MUST KNOW,

179
00:09:00,375 --> 00:09:02,291
IT'S THEIR OWN FAULT FOR
NOT LISTENING TO REASON.

180
00:09:02,375 --> 00:09:04,791
I HAD TO DO IT OR THEY'D
NEVER GET THE HINT.

181
00:09:04,875 --> 00:09:08,791
- ( grunts )
YOU... FAT-HEADED JERK!

182
00:09:08,875 --> 00:09:10,583
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
CUT IT OUT!

183
00:09:10,666 --> 00:09:12,375
- STOP IT!  MILLY!

184
00:09:12,458 --> 00:09:15,750
MILLY!
- YOU ROTTEN INGRATE!

185
00:09:15,833 --> 00:09:18,500
EVIL AND STUPID GOOD
FOR NOTHING, AWFUL SON!

186
00:09:18,583 --> 00:09:20,583
- WHAT?
WHAT'S YOUR PROBLEM?

187
00:09:20,666 --> 00:09:21,666
- ( door opens )

188
00:09:21,750 --> 00:09:22,708
- Old man: WHAT'S ALL
THE COMMOTION?

189
00:09:22,791 --> 00:09:24,458
- HUH?
- WHO'S FIGHTING OUT THERE?

190
00:09:26,083 --> 00:09:27,916
OH.  BADWICK.

191
00:09:29,958 --> 00:09:33,291
- YOU MIND TELLING ME WHAT THE
HELL YOU THINK YOU'RE DOING?

192
00:09:33,375 --> 00:09:35,666
LOOK AT YOU GUYS
STANDING THERE.

193
00:09:35,750 --> 00:09:37,250
YOU HAVEN'T TAKEN CARE
OF A DAMN THING!

194
00:09:37,333 --> 00:09:40,166
- UH, WELL, BADWICK WANTED
JUST ONE MORE CHANCE

195
00:09:40,250 --> 00:09:41,375
TO PERSUADE HIS PARENTS,

196
00:09:41,458 --> 00:09:42,916
SO WE DIDN'T REALLY
SEE ANY HARM IN THAT,

197
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:45,708
SO WE JUST--
- ( growling )

198
00:09:45,791 --> 00:09:48,250
- ( men whimpering )
- HE DID, DID HE?

199
00:09:48,333 --> 00:09:50,250
I HIRED HIM
FOR HIS DILIGENCE,

200
00:09:50,333 --> 00:09:52,750
BUT WHAT'S THE POINT IF HE CAN'T
EVEN KILL HIS OWN PARENTS?

201
00:09:52,833 --> 00:09:54,791
EVIDENTLY, I MADE
AN ERROR IN JUDGMENT,

202
00:09:54,875 --> 00:09:56,375
HAVING ANY FAITH IN HIM.

203
00:09:56,458 --> 00:09:59,250
- ( thundering footsteps )
- HMM?

204
00:09:59,333 --> 00:10:00,750
- ( men yelp )
- WHAT WAS THAT?

205
00:10:00,833 --> 00:10:03,750
- HEY!
- ( mumbling )

206
00:10:03,833 --> 00:10:05,791
- ( men yelp )

207
00:10:06,916 --> 00:10:09,958
- ( crying )
- ( men scream )

208
00:10:11,875 --> 00:10:13,250
- WHAT DO YOU THINK
YOU'RE DOING?

209
00:10:13,333 --> 00:10:15,041
THAT'S MY CAR
YOU JUST DESTROYED!

210
00:10:15,125 --> 00:10:17,208
- ( crying continues )
- OH, WELL, EXCUSE ME!

211
00:10:17,291 --> 00:10:21,500
YOU PROBABLY DID SOMETHING
CROOKED TO GET IT, ANYWAY.

212
00:10:21,583 --> 00:10:23,125
LISTEN, MR. MORGAN,

213
00:10:23,208 --> 00:10:25,125
MY FATHER
AND LITTLE BROTHER'S BAIL MONEY

214
00:10:25,208 --> 00:10:27,250
IS RIDING ON THE SUCCESS
OF THIS LITTLE SCENARIO.

215
00:10:27,333 --> 00:10:28,916
IF YOU TRY TO TAKE IT
OUT OF OUR PAY,

216
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:30,500
YOU'RE GONNA
GET YOURSELF FLATTENED.

217
00:10:30,583 --> 00:10:32,333
- UH, UH... YOU'RE
ABSOLUTELY RIGHT.

218
00:10:32,416 --> 00:10:33,916
I CAN APPRECIATE
THE VALUE OF FAMILY.

219
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:36,250
I DIDN'T LIKE THAT CAR ANYHOW.
