- ( old man groans )

444
00:20:29,708 --> 00:20:30,833
- Old woman: WHAT'S
WRONG, MY DEAR?

445
00:20:30,916 --> 00:20:33,125
- I THINK I MIGHT'VE
PULLED SOMETHING.

446
00:20:33,208 --> 00:20:35,750
IT'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT, DEAR.

447
00:20:35,833 --> 00:20:38,916
- YES, I'M SURE IT WILL.
AND NO MATTER WHAT HAPPENS,

448
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:41,375
WE HAVE TO UNDERSTAND
IT'S WHAT HE WANTS.

449
00:20:41,458 --> 00:20:43,375
WE'LL JUST HAVE TO TRUST HIM.

450
00:20:44,958 --> 00:20:47,541
I DON'T KNOW HOW TO FIND
THE WORDS TO THANK YOU BOTH

451
00:20:47,625 --> 00:20:48,916
FOR WHAT YOU'VE DONE.
- ( both laugh )

452
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:50,416
- ESPECIALLY YOU, MS. MERYL.

453
00:20:50,500 --> 00:20:52,958
I WANT TO SHARE
SOMETHING WITH YOU...

454
00:20:53,041 --> 00:20:55,250
FROM AN OLD MAN
WHO RAISED AN IDIOT SON.

455
00:20:56,833 --> 00:20:58,750
EVERYONE MAKES
THEIR OWN CHOICES.

456
00:20:58,833 --> 00:21:00,458
NOTHING COULD
COMPARE TO THE LOVE

457
00:21:00,541 --> 00:21:02,416
BETWEEN A PARENT AND A CHILD.

458
00:21:02,500 --> 00:21:05,083
LOVE FOR THEM DOESN'T
HAVE TO BE A BURDEN.

459
00:21:05,166 --> 00:21:06,750
INSTEAD OF WORRYING
ABOUT IT,

460
00:21:06,833 --> 00:21:10,625
DO SOMETHING MORE SIMPLE,
YET VERY IMPORTANT.

461
00:21:10,708 --> 00:21:14,916
WALK YOUR OWN PATH
WITH YOUR HEAD HELD HIGH.

462
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:17,208
YOUR LIFE IS THEIR LIFE.

463
00:21:17,291 --> 00:21:19,416
THE FACT THAT
YOU ARE WHO YOU ARE

464
00:21:19,500 --> 00:21:23,750
HELPS THE PEOPLE YOU LOVE
TO LIVE THROUGH YOU.

465
00:21:27,875 --> 00:21:29,666
- Badwick's voice:
I DON'T KNOW WHAT IS SO GREAT

466
00:21:29,750 --> 00:21:31,041
ABOUT THIS STUPID DEED.

467
00:21:31,125 --> 00:21:32,666
( groaning )

468
00:21:40,625 --> 00:21:43,291
- THIS IS THE REAL DEED?
- Badwick: YEAH.

469
00:21:43,375 --> 00:21:44,791
NOW IT'S IN YOUR HANDS.

470
00:21:46,041 --> 00:21:49,083
- HEY!  HOLD ON A MOMENT, SIR.
- HUH?

471
00:21:49,166 --> 00:21:51,750
- THERE SEEMS TO BE ONE MORE
CLAIM TRANSFER IN THE ENVELOPE.

472
00:21:51,833 --> 00:21:53,083
YOU NEED TO LOOK AT IT.

473
00:21:53,166 --> 00:21:55,250
THE BENEFICIARY,
AS WRITTEN HERE,

474
00:21:55,333 --> 00:21:57,916
IS BADWICK.
ISN'T THAT YOU?

475
00:21:58,000 --> 00:21:59,000
- ( gasps )

476
00:22:02,666 --> 00:22:04,291
( breathes shakily )

477
00:22:06,041 --> 00:22:08,833
YES.  THAT'S ME.

478
00:22:11,166 --> 00:22:12,625
- Milly: YIKES!

479
00:22:12,708 --> 00:22:15,500
MERYL, WE'RE NEVER
GONNA MAKE IT!

480
00:22:15,583 --> 00:22:18,458
- I'M SORRY, MILLY! THIS TIME
IT WAS ACTUALLY MY FAULT

481
00:22:18,541 --> 00:22:20,750
FOR STAYING UP
ALL NIGHT WRITING.  AH!

482
00:22:20,833 --> 00:22:21,875
- ( meowing )

483
00:22:26,791 --> 00:22:29,958
- Milly: MERYL!
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

484
00:22:30,041 --> 00:22:32,208
VASH'S BUS IS
GETTING READY TO GO!

485
00:22:32,291 --> 00:22:33,833
THEY'RE GONNA LEAVE
WITHOUT US!

486
00:22:33,916 --> 00:22:35,333
- I'M COMING, I'M COMING!

487
00:22:42,375 --> 00:22:44,250
- ( theme music playing )

488
00:22:51,208 --> 00:22:53,083
( singing in Japanese )

489
00:24:13,541 --> 00:24:15,791
- PEOPLE JUDGE PEOPLE.

490
00:24:15,875 --> 00:24:17,500
LIVES ARE BEING CUT SHORT

491
00:24:17,583 --> 00:24:19,541
BECAUSE OF SOMEONE'S
PERSONAL LOGIC--

492
00:24:19,625 --> 00:24:21,541
MOTHERS, FATHERS, FRIENDS--

493
00:24:21,625 --> 00:24:24,583
THEIR ENTIRE PAST INSTANTLY
VANISHES INTO THIN AIR.

494
00:24:24,666 --> 00:24:27,416
THE QUESTION IS:
SHOULD THIS TAKE PLACE

495
00:24:27,500 --> 00:24:29,083
ON THE WHIM
OF ONE INDIVIDUAL?

496
00:24:29,166 --> 00:24:31,875
A BEAUTIFUL WOMAN
STOOD BEFORE THE CORPSES

497
00:24:31,958 --> 00:24:33,250
OF THE RODERICK THIEVES.

498
00:24:33,333 --> 00:24:35,750
SHE TOLD ME THAT
SHE WAS MERELY DISCARDING 

499
00:24:35,833 --> 00:24:37,375
SOME USELESS GARBAGE.

500
00:24:37,458 --> 00:24:39,125
DOMINIQUE THE CYCLOPS

501
00:24:39,208 --> 00:24:42,333
TOLD ME TO JUST THINK OF IT
AS SPRING CLEANING.

